.TH engraver\-list 1  "engraver 0.1.0"
.SH NAME
engraver\-list \- List available drives
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBengraver list\fR [\fB\-a\fR|\fB\-\-all\fR] [\fB\-\-json\fR] [\fB\-h\fR|\fB\-\-help\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Detect and display available removable drives. Shows drive metadata including
model name, capacity, vendor, serial number, and USB connection speed.
.PP
By default, only removable drives are shown. System drives and internal disks
are hidden to prevent accidental data loss. Use \fB\-\-all\fR to include all drives.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-a\fR, \fB\-\-all\fR
Show all drives including system drives and internal disks.
.TP
\fB\-\-json\fR
Output drive information in JSON format for scripting and automation.
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
Print help information.
.SH EXAMPLES
List removable drives:
.PP
.nf
    engraver list
.fi
.PP
List all drives including system disks:
.PP
.nf
    engraver list \-\-all
.fi
.PP
Output JSON for use in scripts:
.PP
.nf
    engraver list \-\-json
.fi
.PP
Parse JSON output with jq to get device paths:
.PP
.nf
    engraver list \-\-json | jq \-r '.[].path'
.fi
.SH NOTES
USB speed detection shows the connection speed (USB 2.0 vs 3.0) and warns
if a USB 3.0\-capable device is connected at USB 2.0 speed. This can indicate
the device is plugged into a USB 2.0 port.
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBengraver\fR(1), \fBengraver\-write\fR(1), \fBengraver\-benchmark\fR(1)
